- What are you even
talking about?

26:46.739 --> 26:48.007
- I don't know, I'm just saying
words that I've heard before.

26:48.040 --> 26:51.911
- What now?
- Well, we have to torch it.

26:51.944 --> 26:53.946
- You wanna blow up a car?
- We're not doing that.

26:53.980 --> 26:56.716
- Beth, it has my digital
fingerprints on it!

26:56.749 --> 26:58.150
- In the middle
of rush hour traffic,

26:58.184 --> 27:01.721
you wanna blow up a car.
- Do you have a better idea?

27:01.754 --> 27:03.856
[quirky music]

27:06.793 --> 27:08.027
You know, I just--
- Nope.

27:10.930 --> 27:12.899
- I just wanna--
- Nuh-uh.

27:15.067 --> 27:18.971
[splashing]

27:19.005 --> 27:20.973
[melancholy music]

27:21.007 --> 27:27.880
[cell phone rings]

27:33.786 --> 27:35.221
- Hello?

27:35.254 --> 27:39.726
- Hello?
Hello?

27:39.759 --> 27:43.696
Hello, did I lose you?
Hello?

27:43.730 --> 27:45.131
- Hello?

27:45.164 --> 27:47.033
- Hi, it's Clare Davis.

27:47.066 --> 27:49.201
I'm here for your custody
evaluation.

27:49.235 --> 27:51.203
- Jesus, my God!
Oh, my God!

27:51.237 --> 27:52.939
Okay.
- It's almost 7:00.

27:52.972 --> 27:54.774
- Hi, hi, I'm so sorry.

27:54.807 --> 27:56.142
I'm just running
a little bit late.

27:56.175 --> 27:59.946
I'm having a little bit of...
Car trouble.

27:59.979 --> 28:01.213
- Well, how far away are you?

28:01.247 --> 28:02.782
- Not far!

28:15.494 --> 28:15.828
.

28:15.862 --> 28:16.395
- This is us at Six Flags.

28:17.964 --> 28:19.732
My mom looks kind of weird
because she just barfed.

28:19.766 --> 28:21.300
- [laughs]

28:21.333 --> 28:24.804
- Yeah, I, uh, I always do
after Big Blue, right?

28:24.837 --> 28:26.472
- [laughs]
She still goes on it

28:26.505 --> 28:28.507
with me anyway.
- Uh, hi.

28:28.540 --> 28:30.910
I'm Annie.
I'm so, so, so sorry

28:30.943 --> 28:36.182
I, uh, am so late.
My day just got crazy.

28:36.215 --> 28:37.449
- Oh, how so?

28:37.483 --> 28:39.451
- She does a lot
of charity work.

28:39.485 --> 28:41.988
- With kids.
Yeah, I love kids.

28:42.021 --> 28:44.356
You know, sick kids.
And healthy kids.

28:44.390 --> 28:45.925
I mean, who doesn't love
healthy kids?

28:45.958 --> 28:48.795
Wow, I can't stop
saying "kids."

28:48.828 --> 28:50.196
- What kind of children
do you work with?

28:50.229 --> 28:51.798
- Mentally disabled.
- Cancer...

28:51.831 --> 28:53.800
Kind.

28:53.833 --> 28:57.904
Cancer and they are also
mentally disabled, yeah.

28:57.937 --> 29:00.807
So it's really sad.

29:00.840 --> 29:04.443
- Wow, yeah, uh,
well, you must be exhausted.

29:04.476 --> 29:06.478
Um, I'll make this quick.

29:06.512 --> 29:09.816
I just have a few standard
questions.

29:09.849 --> 29:10.983
- Shrimp?

29:15.421 --> 29:17.256
- [sighs]

29:19.391 --> 29:22.829
Kids just went down.
- Okay, good.

29:23.996 --> 29:25.865
- Now we got business.

29:27.033 --> 29:29.401
- Can we please
do this tomorrow?

29:29.435 --> 29:30.769
- Nope.

29:32.839 --> 29:35.942
- I'm sorry.
I overreacted.

29:35.975 --> 29:39.378
She can come over for dinner.
Once, okay?

29:39.411 --> 29:40.512
- Nope.

29:41.948 --> 29:43.515
- What more do you
want from me?

29:46.953 --> 29:49.455
- Your hands where
I can see them.

29:49.488 --> 29:52.058
- [chuckles]
Seriously?

29:52.091 --> 29:53.826
- Oh, yeah.

29:53.860 --> 29:56.095
- Babe, I'm legit so tired.

29:56.128 --> 30:00.499
- Yeah, but you just came back
from a girls' trip.

30:00.532 --> 30:02.935
- Trust me,
it was not relaxing.

30:02.969 --> 30:04.503
- Oh, you could just lie there.

30:11.911 --> 30:14.413
- I was stupid.
- I know.

30:14.446 --> 30:17.416
[calm music]

30:17.449 --> 30:20.019
*

30:20.052 --> 30:21.487
- I love you.

30:21.520 --> 30:23.322
*

30:23.355 --> 30:24.857
- I know.

30:24.891 --> 30:27.559
*

30:27.593 --> 30:29.561
- Neatest homework packets.

30:29.595 --> 30:31.130
- What does that even mean,
right?

30:31.163 --> 30:33.599
- Your daughter is one
impressive young lady.

30:33.632 --> 30:35.467
Okay, I just need
to take a quick peek

30:35.501 --> 30:38.337
in your mom's bedroom,
and then I am out of here.

30:38.370 --> 30:41.040
- No, wait.
- Sweetie!

30:41.073 --> 30:42.574
- Oh, my God!
- What happened?

30:42.608 --> 30:43.976
- Nothing.
- Okay, that doesn't look

30:44.010 --> 30:45.611
like nothing.
- It's fine.

30:45.644 --> 30:47.013
- How long has this been
bleeding like this?

30:47.046 --> 30:49.115
- Since I made the shrimp.

30:49.148 --> 30:52.018
- Okay, how long did you
leave her alone today?

30:52.051 --> 30:53.920
- I have to get you a Band-Aid.

30:53.953 --> 30:56.588
- We don't have any.
I already looked.

30:56.622 --> 30:58.925
- If this is a latchkey
situation,

30:58.958 --> 31:00.492
I'm gonna have to report it.

31:00.526 --> 31:02.995
- It's totally not.
- Honey, it's okay, Sadie.

31:03.029 --> 31:05.932
- She never leaves me alone.
- Sadie.

31:05.965 --> 31:09.501
Normally, I don't.
But today I had to.

31:09.535 --> 31:11.537
I had something really
important come up,

31:11.570 --> 31:13.539
and I--I just lost track
of the time.

31:13.572 --> 31:17.509
- Because of the mentally
disabled cancer kids?

31:17.543 --> 31:19.445
- Sadie, I have to take you
to a hospital.

31:19.478 --> 31:21.013
I... I think you need stitches.

31:21.047 --> 31:25.084
- Your car has the boot.
The boot.

31:25.117 --> 31:27.353
- Um...

31:27.386 --> 31:32.992
I'm kind of in between vehicles
at the moment.

31:33.025 --> 31:35.494
Any chance you could
give us a lift?

31:36.728 --> 31:39.098
- Okay, come on, boo.
Oh, my goodness.

31:39.131 --> 31:41.200
Oh.
[creaking]

31:41.233 --> 31:44.971
Oh, ooh,
your feet smell

31:45.004 --> 31:46.939
like you're a high school
football player.

31:46.973 --> 31:51.010
- Mmm-mmm.
- Hey, I love you so much.

31:51.043 --> 31:53.379
You know that?

31:53.412 --> 31:55.982
I love you all the way
to the moon and back.

31:56.015 --> 31:57.149
[kisses]

31:57.183 --> 32:01.087
*

32:01.120 --> 32:05.024
Hey.
Good night, boo.

32:05.057 --> 32:06.225
[kisses]

32:06.258 --> 32:13.499
*

32:15.667 --> 32:19.238
Hey, would you mind if
I steal some cold cuts?

32:19.271 --> 32:20.639
Getting pretty tired of eating

32:20.672 --> 32:22.641
hotel vending machine
for dinner.

32:22.674 --> 32:23.642
- Sure.

32:23.675 --> 32:24.676
*

32:24.710 --> 32:26.112
- Thanks.

32:28.447 --> 32:30.216
- So, how many cars
did they take?

32:30.249 --> 32:33.752
- Oh, don't know yet.
Still doing intake.

32:33.785 --> 32:35.621
Which, of course,
I have to pay for.

32:35.654 --> 32:37.156
- What about insurance?

32:37.189 --> 32:39.491
- Oh, even with a claim,
we take a hit.

32:39.525 --> 32:41.493
- Oh.
Sorry.

32:41.527 --> 32:44.063
- [laughs]
It's not your fault.

32:45.197 --> 32:48.467
Oh, this is a lifesaver.
Thank you.

32:48.500 --> 32:50.669
[clears throat]
Hey, so--

32:50.702 --> 32:52.704
[clears throat]

32:52.738 --> 32:56.708
I have been thinking about our
little sitch.

32:56.742 --> 32:59.445
And...

32:59.478 --> 33:04.716
If we were smart,
we would get back together.

33:04.750 --> 33:05.784
[stammers]
Just hear me out.

33:05.817 --> 33:07.486
Okay, so look.

33:07.519 --> 33:10.789
I would totally wanna
divorce my ass, too.

33:10.822 --> 33:13.225
But in the end,
I wouldn't.

33:13.259 --> 33:15.027
I would not.

33:15.061 --> 33:16.195
- Why not?

33:16.228 --> 33:18.064
- Why not?

33:18.097 --> 33:21.467
Because of the ancient
rule of two.

33:21.500 --> 33:23.635
- The ancient rule of two?
- Yes.

33:23.669 --> 33:27.073
Two houses, two mortgages,
two--two cable bills.

33:27.106 --> 33:28.307
- Okay.

33:28.340 --> 33:29.708
- Two water sewage
garbage fees?

33:29.741 --> 33:31.510
I mean, that--that--
that's craziness.

33:31.543 --> 33:33.045
- Wow, it is so romantic,

33:33.079 --> 33:35.214
the way you're wooing me
right now, honestly.

33:35.247 --> 33:36.648
- I'm not wooing you.

33:36.682 --> 33:39.651
I'm begging you
not to leave me.

33:39.685 --> 33:41.520
- By way of sewage fees.

33:41.553 --> 33:44.090
- Well, I was gonna mention

33:44.123 --> 33:45.824
that you are the
love of my life.

33:45.857 --> 33:47.259
And that I wish everything
could go back

33:47.293 --> 33:48.760
to the way it was.

33:48.794 --> 33:51.630
Because I had no damn idea
how good I had it

33:51.663 --> 33:54.700
until it was gone,
but then I thought that sounded

33:54.733 --> 33:57.736
kind of cheesy,
so I decided to focus

33:57.769 --> 33:59.638
on the cable bill,

33:59.671 --> 34:02.108
which kind of isn't really
playing out

34:02.141 --> 34:04.042
like I thought it was gonna.

34:06.678 --> 34:10.282
Look, I--I know you
hate me right now.

34:13.119 --> 34:15.354
- I don't hate you.

34:15.387 --> 34:17.589
- [scoffs]

34:20.292 --> 34:21.760
Good.

34:23.262 --> 34:25.864
Look, I just--I just don't
think we have

34:25.897 --> 34:27.833
much of a choice.

34:30.702 --> 34:32.304
- There's always a choice.

34:32.338 --> 34:36.242
[Gin Wigmore's
"Written In The Water"]

34:36.275 --> 34:40.812
- * I was born by the devil
I was left here to die *

34:40.846 --> 34:45.817
