35:10.676 --> 35:13.312
* Drown my sorrows
in someone *

35:13.345 --> 35:15.781
* In the hope
I leave this hell *

35:15.814 --> 35:20.386
* I was told not to love him
I was told not to try *

35:20.419 --> 35:25.357
* I was lonely the only
'til he said he'd be mine *

35:25.391 --> 35:30.429
* He will leave me for younger
he will leave me to cry *

35:30.462 --> 35:33.165
* Cut the knife
a little deeper *

35:33.199 --> 35:35.401
* Count the days I survived

35:35.434 --> 35:37.903
* Yeah it's written
in the water *

35:37.936 --> 35:40.339
* Yeah it's everywhere I go

35:40.372 --> 35:42.874
* Telling me that I should
leave you *

35:42.908 --> 35:45.344
* Like I did two
times before *

35:45.377 --> 35:47.879
* I'd be fine if I met you

35:47.913 --> 35:50.349
* And you'd still have
had to roam *

35:50.382 --> 35:52.918
* Give me one kiss
for the road *

35:52.951 --> 35:56.388
* Now it's time I let you go

35:56.422 --> 35:58.424
*

35:58.457 --> 36:00.226
* I will run to the river

36:00.259 --> 36:02.794
* I will won't be
what you like *

36:02.828 --> 36:05.431
* Yeah,
it's one kiss for the road *

36:05.464 --> 36:08.267
* And it's time I let you go

36:10.769 --> 36:10.936
.

36:10.969 --> 36:11.303
[door creaks]

36:19.811 --> 36:22.781
- Hey, I'm gonna call
that fancy lawyer.

36:22.814 --> 36:24.783
See if she can
get us a do-over.

36:28.554 --> 36:31.390
No shrimp this time.
I'm gonna go big.

36:31.423 --> 36:33.559
Like crab legs.

36:33.592 --> 36:36.328
[bottle opening]
- [sniffs]

36:41.400 --> 36:43.669
- I'm sorry.

36:43.702 --> 36:46.305
I suck.

36:46.338 --> 36:48.507
[sighs]

36:48.540 --> 36:50.642
Do you hear me?
I--

36:50.676 --> 36:52.811
I said I'm sorry.

36:52.844 --> 36:54.580
I suck.

36:57.583 --> 36:58.917
- Where were you?

37:01.387 --> 37:05.757
- I had to do something
really, really important.

37:05.791 --> 37:08.494
- What's more important
than me?

37:08.527 --> 37:10.929
[melancholy music]

37:10.962 --> 37:16.535
*

37:16.568 --> 37:20.572
- There is literally nothing
in my entire life

37:20.606 --> 37:23.642
that is more important
to me than you.

37:23.675 --> 37:24.876
- I'm going to bed.

37:24.910 --> 37:29.581
*

37:29.615 --> 37:31.383
- Tell me the Lord is good,
now.

37:31.417 --> 37:32.651
He's good!
[applause]

37:32.684 --> 37:34.520
He's good, I tell you.
The Lord is good.

37:34.553 --> 37:35.854
Hey, man, is there anyone else

37:35.887 --> 37:37.556
who wants to testify
this morning?

37:37.589 --> 37:38.757
Anybody?

37:38.790 --> 37:40.792
- I would.
- Ah.

37:40.826 --> 37:43.929
- You would?
- I would.

37:43.962 --> 37:45.464
- Sister Ruby.

37:46.932 --> 37:48.734
- Hello, everyone.

37:48.767 --> 37:53.572
Um, I would just like to follow
up on the other day.

37:53.605 --> 37:56.342
To be totally honest,
I am not feeling

37:56.375 --> 37:58.477
super good about it.

37:58.510 --> 38:02.914
Sheila, you went above and
beyond for our little girl.

38:02.948 --> 38:05.484
I don't even know how you put
together all that money.

38:05.517 --> 38:07.686
You're still at the salon,
right?

38:08.787 --> 38:11.557
- I've saved here and there
over the years.

38:12.791 --> 38:14.893
- Well, listen.

38:14.926 --> 38:19.498
I realize that I reacted badly.

38:19.531 --> 38:23.602
Because I have a hard time
taking charity.

38:23.635 --> 38:25.637
Pride is a sin,
as we all know.

38:25.671 --> 38:26.838
all: Amen.

38:26.872 --> 38:28.674
- So I would just like
to say something

38:28.707 --> 38:30.376
that I should have said before.

38:30.409 --> 38:32.511
Which is thank you.

38:32.544 --> 38:35.514
[applause]
Thank you for the money.

38:35.547 --> 38:36.948
- You're welcome.

38:38.417 --> 38:42.421
- And thank you for offering
to drive the kids

38:42.454 --> 38:43.855
home from school
when I'm at work.

38:43.889 --> 38:45.857
And thanks for offering

38:45.891 --> 38:48.794
to babysit so that we
can have a date night.

38:48.827 --> 38:53.532
And offering to do the laundry
and, oh, my God, the groceries.

38:53.565 --> 38:55.501
At Whole Foods, no less.
- Seriously?

38:55.534 --> 38:58.770
- Because this woman--
This woman only buys

38:58.804 --> 39:01.473
organic, people.
[applause]

39:01.507 --> 39:02.808
- I don't even know
what to say.

39:02.841 --> 39:05.411
- There's nothing to say.

39:05.444 --> 39:06.778
But thank you.

39:06.812 --> 39:08.747
- Got it.

39:08.780 --> 39:10.482
- I know you do.

39:10.516 --> 39:13.419
[applause]
- Praise the Lord.

39:13.452 --> 39:15.721
- God bless you, Sheila.

39:15.754 --> 39:18.857
- Sometimes our prayer simply
needs to be "Lord Jesus,

39:18.890 --> 39:21.660
"help me to learn
to be generous.

39:21.693 --> 39:24.963
To labor and to not
seek reward."

39:24.996 --> 39:28.567
Let us all simply say--
all: Amen.

39:28.600 --> 39:31.703
[shopping carts rattling]

39:42.814 --> 39:44.916
- Well, look who's finally
using the pen.

39:44.950 --> 39:48.487
- Yeah, it just felt
a little crispy.

39:48.520 --> 39:50.856
- Hmm, let me try.
- Uh, no, I'm sure it's fine.

39:50.889 --> 39:52.090
I mean--
- Let me see.

40:14.646 --> 40:16.114
- It's legit.

40:18.884 --> 40:21.119
Good thing,
'cause customer's long gone.

40:21.152 --> 40:25.557
Next time try checking before
they leave the store.

40:25.591 --> 40:26.792
- Good pro tip.

40:27.993 --> 40:32.831
- Oh, uh, do anything fun
on your day off?

40:32.864 --> 40:35.534
- Just hung out with my kid.

40:35.567 --> 40:36.668
- Is that all?

40:38.136 --> 40:41.607
- Is there something
you wanna ask me?

40:41.640 --> 40:43.074
- Just making conversation.

40:45.744 --> 40:48.714
[gentle music]

40:48.747 --> 40:55.821
*

41:35.193 --> 41:36.895
- Are you awake?

41:36.928 --> 41:44.002
*

42:05.156 --> 42:07.826
- You know the traditions is
Jordans over a phone line,

42:07.859 --> 42:09.728
right?

42:09.761 --> 42:11.763
- I only had pumps.

42:11.797 --> 42:13.164
- Fair enough.

42:18.103 --> 42:21.206
So what'd you wanna talk
to me about?

42:21.239 --> 42:24.209
[gentle music continues]

42:24.242 --> 42:31.683
*
